GOAL: ALLOWING FLASK APP AND MYSQL DATABASE TO TALK USING A DOCKER NETWORK

    STEP 1 - CREATE A NETWORK 
        "docker network create flask-mysql-net"
        this is the virtual switch bothy containers connect to.
    
    STEP 2 - RUN MySQL CONTAINER   
        - [docker run -d \
        --name mysql-db \
        --network flask-mysql-net \
        -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=rootpass \
        -e MYSQL_DATABASE=mydb \
        mysql:8]

        WHAT THIS DOES
            [--name mysql-db]: this becomes your host name in flask 
            [MYSQL_DATABASE=mydb] : auto-creates a database 
            [rootpass]: root password
    
    STEP 3 - INSTALL MySQL DRIVER IN FLASK
        add this to the requirements.txt and rebuild later
        [flask
        mysql-connector-python]

    STEP 4 - UPDATE FLASK APP
        replace app.py code with:
        [from flask import Flask
        import mysql.connector

        app = Flask(__name__)

        def get_connection():
        return mysql.connector.connect(
        host="mysql-db",
        user="root",
        password="rootpass",
        database="mydb"
        )

        @app.route("/")
        def home():
        conn = get_connection()
        cursor = conn.cursor()

        cursor.execute("CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS test (id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50))")
        cursor.execute("INSERT INTO test (name) VALUES ('Hello from Flask')")
        conn.commit()

        cursor.execute("SELECT * FROM test")
        data = cursor.fetchall()

        return str(data)

        if __name__ == "__main__":
        app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5002)]

STEP 5 - BUILD FLASK IMAGE
    - [docker build -t flask-app .]

STEP 6 - RUN FLASK CONTAINER
    - [docker run -d \
    --name flask-app \
    --network flask-mysql-net \
    -p 5002:5002 \
    flask-app]

STEP 7 - TEST IT 
    OPEN: 
        - http://localhost:5002
    YOU SHOULD SEE:
        - [(1, 'Hello from Flask')]

COMMON ERRORS (AND FIXES)
    - "CANNOT CONNECT TO MySQL"
    FIX: make sure both are on same network.
        - [docker network inspect flask-mysql-net]
    - "ACCESS DENIED FOR USER ROOT"
    FIX: check passwords match
        - password="rootpass"
    - "MySQL NOT READY YET"
    FIX: wait 10–15 seconds after starting MySQL, Sometimes Flask starts too fast.
